description:
Top Secret America: 911 to the Boston Bombings

Sociopolitical Documentary hosted by Will Lyman, published by PBS broadcasted as part of PBS Frontline series in 2013 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

FRONTLINE producer Michael Kirk (Bush's War, The Torture Question) teams up with Pulitzer Prize-winning Washington Post journalist Dana Priest to reveal an unprecedented yet largely invisible legacy of 9/11: the creation of a vast maze of clandestine government and private agencies designed to hunt terrorists and prevent future attacks on the United States. This is a updated version of the original &quot;Frontline Top Secret America&quot; from 2011.

